FBIS4-35154 "drlat125_m_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 Brazil President Orders Minimum Wage Increase for 1 Sep President Orders Minimum Wage Increase for 1 Sep PY2806201594 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 1000 GMT 28 Jun 94 PY2806201594 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Portuguese BFN [Report by Luiz Augusto Mendonca in Brasilia] [Text] The minimum wage will be $70 on 1 September. President Itamar Franco made this decision following a meeting with the finance, labor, and social security ministers, and the federal administration secretary. Labor Minister Marcelo Pimentel later said that by the end of October the government will send Congress a draft bill outlining a new minimum wage policy. President Itamar said military and public servants will receive a salary adjustment soon after the implementation of the real. The president said the date for the wage increase has yet to be established, but it will be implemented even if he has to fight with his economic ministers.
